{"cursor":"7790","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Weapon|is_ranged=yes| |name= Type 24 / Type Zhongzheng |image=\n|caption= Type Zhongzheng rifle/Type 24 rifle |type= Bolt action rifle |origin=\n|era= World War II |platform= Individual |used_by= National Revolutionary Army,\nChinese Red Army, various Chinese Warlords |wars= Second Sino-Japanese\nWar, Chinese Civil War, Korean War |target= Personnel |design_date=\n1935 [http://www.secwar.net/News/2007128154426.html\nå¥æå«å¹´ï¼ï¼ä¸­æ­£å¼æ­¥éªæª.] Retrieved on August 2, 2008. (Simplified Chinese)\n||manufacturer=Kunghsien, Hanyang, Jinglin and Canton Arsenals\n|production_date= 1935â1950 |service= 1935â1980s |part_length= |cartridge=\n8Ã57mm IS |feed= 5-round stripper clip, internal magazine |action= Bolt action\n|rate= 15 rounds per minute |velocity= 810 m/s (2,657 ft/s) |weight= |length=\n|range= |variants= Chiang Kai-shek rifle Type 1, Chiang Kai-shek rifle Type 2\n|number= 500,000â600,000 }}\n\nThe 'Type Zhongzheng rifle' (ä¸­æ­£å¼), also known as the Chiang Kai-shek/Jiang\nJieshi Rifle, Generalissimo Rifle, and Type 24 (äºåå¼) after the Chinese\nGeneralissimo Chiang Kai-shek, was a Chinese-made copy of the modified German\nMauser Standard Modell of 1933, [http://www.rocchi.org/fucili/schede/mausercina2.htm Mauser\ncinese modello 1933 \"standard modell\".] Retrieved on August 3, 2008.  the\nforerunner of the Karabiner 98k. Pre-production of the Chiang Kai-shek rifle\nstarted in August 1935 (year 24 of the Republican calendar, hence the Type 24).\nIt was later renamed the Type Zhongzheng and was in full scale production as\nearly as late 1935. It was designated the Type 79 by the Chinese Communists and\nwould often have the ideograph of Chiang defaced by them.\nAlthough the Hanyang 88 rifle was produced in greater numbers than the Type\nZhongzheng, the full standardization of the Type Zhongzheng rifle only started\nduring the Second Sino-Japanese war.\n\nIn a ten-year period, over half a million weapons were produced. The weapon's\nlast major war was in Korea, in the 1950s.\n","linknr":235,"url":"Chiang_Kai-shek_rifle","recorded":1375090683,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Chiang_Kai-shek_rifle&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Chiang_Kai-shek_rifle&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:En-CKS_rifle-1.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/En-CKS_rifle-1.jpg/300px-En-CKS_rifle-1.jpg","/wiki/Bolt_action","/wiki/Rifle","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/Flag_of_the_Republic_of_China.svg/23px-Flag_of_the_Republic_of_China.svg.png","/wiki/Taiwan","/wiki/National_Revolutionary_Army","/wiki/People%27s_Liberation_Army","/wiki/Warlord_era","/wiki/Second_Sino-Japanese_War","/wiki/Chinese_Civil_War","/wiki/Korean_War","#cite_note-History-1","/w/index.php?title=Kunghsien_Arsenal&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Hanyang_Arsenal","/w/index.php?title=Jinglin_Arsenal&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=Canton_Arsenal&action=edit&redlink=1","#cite_note-History-1","/wiki/Gun_barrel","/wiki/Cartridge_(firearms)","/wiki/7.92%C3%9757mm_Mauser","/wiki/Firearm_action","/wiki/Bolt_action","/wiki/Rate_of_fire","/wiki/Muzzle_velocity","/wik